# Albion Killbot

Discord bot + web dashboard for Albion Online kill/death tracking. MIT licensed monorepo with two packages: `server/` and `dashboard/`.

## Server modes

Started via `server/bin/start.js` with `--mode` or `MODE` env var:

| Mode | Role |
|------|------|
| `crawler` | Fetches kills from Albion APIs, publishes to AMQP |
| `bot` | Consumes queue, posts Discord embeds |
| `api` | Express REST API + Swagger for dashboard and webhooks |

## Local development

Prefer Docker via [`devenv/ctl.sh`](devenv/ctl.sh). Link it once from the repo root: `npm link --prefix devenv` (then use `ctl` globally), or run `./devenv/ctl.sh` directly.

Env: `server/.env` needs at least `DISCORD_TOKEN`; MongoDB, AMQP, and other vars per `server/src/config/default.js`.

### `ctl` commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `ctl start` | Start the full stack (detached) |
| `ctl start [component]` | Start one service |
| `ctl stop` | Stop the full stack |
| `ctl stop [component]` | Stop and remove one service |
| `ctl restart` | Restart the stack |
| `ctl restart [component]` | Restart one service |
| `ctl build [component]` | Build Docker image(s) |
| `ctl logs [component]` | Follow logs (`ctrl+c` to exit) |
| `ctl shell [component]` | Open an interactive bash shell in a container |
| `ctl exec [component] [cmd...]` | Run a one-off command in a container |
| `ctl migrate` | Run database migrations |
| `ctl cmd <compose-args>` | Passthrough to `docker compose` |
| `ctl help` | List commands and components |

**App components** (for `shell`, `exec`, `logs`, `restart`): `crawler`, `bot`, `api`, `dashboard`.

Infrastructure also runs in compose (`mongodb`, `amqp`, `nginx`, `stripe`) but app work usually targets the four components above.

### Running package scripts in containers

Prefer `ctl exec` over host `npm` when the dev stack is up — Node/tooling versions match the container and paths resolve correctly.

```bash
# Dashboard — lint, typecheck, format (before finishing dashboard UI work)
ctl exec dashboard npm run lint
ctl exec dashboard npx tsc --noEmit
ctl exec dashboard npm run prettier
ctl exec dashboard npx prettier --write src/pages/home/

# Server — lint and format
ctl exec api npm run lint
ctl exec api npm run prettier
```

Use `ctl logs api`, `ctl logs bot`, etc. when debugging runtime issues. Full restart when subprocesses misbehave: `ctl restart` or `ctl restart [component]`.

**Dashboard dev server:** Use **Albion Nexus - Development** for local UI testing and demos (`/dashboard/1447669162917761047/...`). Do not use Albion Killbot or other guilds unless explicitly asked.

## CI expectations

PRs run lint + prettier per package (`server-ci.yml`, `dashboard-ci.yml`). Match existing style before submitting.

## Scope when changing code

- Server-only logic → `server/src/`
- Dashboard UI → `dashboard/src/`
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`, tokens, keys)
